Interface GIEnumParameter

  • All Superinterfaces:
    GIModelObject, GIParameter<java.lang.String>, GIParamOrRef, IViewedModelObject

    @NotThreadSafe
 @PublishedApi(value=ADDITIONS_ALLOWED)
public interface GIEnumParameter
extends GIParameter<java.lang.String>

      • getAsCustomEnum

        @PublishedMethod
<CUSTOM_ENUM extends java.lang.Enum<CUSTOM_ENUM>> CUSTOM_ENUM getAsCustomEnum(java.lang.Class<CUSTOM_ENUM> destClass)
        Gets the value of the GEnumeration as a custom enum literal.

        If the Class destClass implements the IModelEnum interface. The literals are mapped via these information form the IModelEnum interface.

        Type Parameters:
        CUSTOM_ENUM - the enum class Generic
        Parameters:
        destClass - the destination enum class
        Returns:
        the literal mapped via the destClass Parameters
        Throws:
        BswmdModelParameterHasIllegalValueException -
        • If the values is not mappable to the custom enum
        See Also:
        ModelEnumUtil

      • setValueMdf

        @PublishedMethod
void setValueMdf(GIEnumParameter.GIEnumClass newValue)
        Convenience method to set the textual value of the GIEnumParameter. This method checks if the specified parameters definition object is available and sets the value only if its definition type is integer. If the parameter has no definition the parameter is set in either case.
        Parameters:
        newValue -
        Throws:
        BswmdModelNotExistsException -
        • if the parameter does not exist in the MDF model
